    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_kad" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kad</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kadæ</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>слава</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>glory</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>почесть</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>honour</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>kadǵyn</orth></form>
                        <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                    <q>славный</q>
                                </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                    <q>famous</q>
                                </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                    <q>чтимый</q>
                                </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                    <q>honoured</q>
                                </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>ægad</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>бесславный</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>infamous</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>fydælty kad</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>слава предков</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the glory of the ancestors</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dæ nomyl, dæ kadyl næ baryn mæxt</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>с твоим именем, твоей славой я себя не равняю</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I don't equate myself with your name, your glory</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kadmæ bælgæjæ ægadæj mælæm</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>стремясь к славе, мы погибаем в бесславии</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>striving for glory, we perish in shame</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>39</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ka din ne skænʒænæj kadæ?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кто не воздаст тебе почестей?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>кто не воздаст тебе почестей?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Wadž."
                            /><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран. *%ikāta-%i. Лексикализованное причастие от не
                    сохранившегося в осетинском глагола *%ikay-%i, *%ičay-%i ‘воздавать должное’ и
                    пр., и.е. *%ik˳ei-%i с исходным значением ‘смотреть’, ‘обращать внимание’
                            (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope>636
                            сл.</biblScope></bibl>). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kay-</w>
                        <gloss><q>воздавать должное</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>kava-</w>
                        <gloss><q>воздаяние</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>kāta-</w></mentioned> в %ixratu-kāta-%i ‘прославленный мудростью’,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čāyati</w>
                        <gloss><q>оказывает внимание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>чтит</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>čayate</w>
                        <gloss><q>воздает</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>мстит</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">каяти ся</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="orv"><lang/>
                        <w>каяти</w>
                        <gloss><q>мстить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sr"><lang/>
                        <w>kajati</w>
                        <gloss><q>мстить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>каяться</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">чаяти</w>
                        <gloss><q>ждать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>надеяться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>τἰω</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>τείω</w>
                        <gloss><q>ценю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>чту</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>τιμή</w>
                        <gloss><q>почесть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>воздаяние</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Этот же корень наличен в ос.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cyt"/> | %icitæ%i ‘почет’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ævǵīd"/> (%iæv-gīd%i) ‘порука’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kīnæ"/> (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_kenæ"/>) ‘месть’, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_koj"/> ‘молва’ (отношение %ikad%i || %ikoj%i такое
                    же, как %iancad%i || %iæncoj%i, %ifællad%i || %ifælloj%i). — Отношение
                    перечисленных слов к их предполагаемым исходным формам представляется в
                    следующем виде:%n%ikad%i ← *%ikata-%i%ikoj%i ← *%ikan(у)а-%i%ikīnæ%i ←
                    *%ikaina-%i%i(æv)ǵīd%i ← *%i(аbi)kaita-%i%icyt%i ← *%ičiva-%iПроизводным от
                    %ikad%i является, по-видимому, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kadæg"/>
                    ‘героическая сага’, ‘былина’. — %sBailey%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>XIII 396</biblScope></bibl>) относит
                    сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из иран.) </note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en">(from Iranian) </note><w>nkʼ atʼ(*ni-kata)</w>
                        <gloss><q>внимание</q></gloss></mentioned> и привлекает также собственное
                    имя, встречающееся на кушанских монетах, — %iKadphises%i, %iКаdaphes%i из
                    *%ikāta-paisa%i ‘славного вида’ (ср. по образованию Σπαργαπίσης, Ἀριαπείυης:
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>175</biblScope></bibl>). — С ос. %ikad%i связаны, по-видимому,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>kad-eba</w>
                        <gloss><q>хвастать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>хвастовство</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>kad-ili</w>
                        <gloss><q>хвастовство</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>предмет гордости</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>kad-il-oba</w>
                        <gloss><q>гордиться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>si-kad-uli</w>
                        <gloss><q>слава</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>гордость</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>kad</w>
                        <gloss><q>приз</q></gloss></mentioned> также сближается с осетинским (%bГ е
                    н к о, ЗКВ V 722%b). — Другие этимологии: Шегрен (84) — араб. %iqadr%i ‘цена’,
                    ‘достоинство’; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                            /><biblScope>(II 49)</biblScope></bibl>: „м.б. сближается с авест.
                    %ikāta-%i ‘любимый’, ‘любящий’, прич. страд. от %ikā-%i ‘желать’“. Ср. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_kadæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_koj"/>,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kīnæ"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cyt"/>,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævǵīd"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to Iranian *%ikāta-%i. It is a lexicalized
                    participle from not preserved Ossetic verb *%ikay-%i, *%ičay-%i ‘to give due’
                    etc., Indo-European *%ik˳ei-%i with the initial meaning ‘to look’, ‘to pay
                    attention’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope>636
                            сл.</biblScope></bibl>). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kay-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to give due</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>kava-</w>
                        <gloss><q>requitak</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>kāta-</w></mentioned> в %ixratu-kāta-%i ‘glorified by wisdom’,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čāyati</w>
                        <gloss><q>(he) favours</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>(he) honours</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>čayate</w>
                        <gloss><q>(he) gives (due)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>to take revenge</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>kajti sę</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="orv"><lang/>
                        <w>каяти</w>
                        <gloss><q>to take revenge</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sr"><lang/>
                        <w>kajati</w>
                        <gloss><q>to take revenge</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>kajatʼsja</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>čajati</w>
                        <gloss><q>to wait</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>to hope</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>τἰω</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>τείω</w>
                        <gloss><q>(I) value</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>(I) honour</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>τιμή</w>
                        <gloss><q>honour</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>requital</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The same root is found in
                    Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cyt"/> | %icitæ%i ‘respect’, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ævǵīd"/> (%iæv-gīd%i) ‘bail’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kīnæ"/> (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_kenæ"/>) ‘revenge’,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_koj"/> ‘rumour’ (the relation %ikad%i ||
                    %ikoj%i is the same as %iancad%i || %iæncoj%i, %ifællad%i || %ifælloj%i). — The
                    relation between the words listed above and their assumed initial forms is as
                    follows:%n%ikad%i ← *%ikata-%i%ikoj%i ← *%ikan(у)а-%i%ikīnæ%i ←
                    *%ikaina-%i%i(æv)ǵīd%i ← *%i(аbi)kaita-%i%icyt%i ← *%ičiva-%iThe word <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_kadæg"/> ‘героическая сага’, ‘былина’ is apparently
                    derived from %ikad%i. — %sBailey%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"
                            /><biblScope>XIII 396</biblScope></bibl>) attributes to this root
                        <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из иран.) </note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en">(from Iranian) </note><w>nkʼ atʼ(*ni-kata)</w>
                        <gloss><q>attention</q></gloss></mentioned>, he also appeals to a proper
                    name, which can be encountered on Kushan coins, — %iKadphises%i, %iКаdaphes%i
                    from *%ikāta-paisa%i ‘glorious’ (cf. on derivation Σπαργαπίσης, Ἀριαπείυης:
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>175</biblScope></bibl>). —Ossetic %ikad%i is apparently related
                    to <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>kad-eba</w>
                        <gloss><q>to boast</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>boasting</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>kad-ili</w>
                        <gloss><q>boasting</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>boast</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>kad-il-oba</w>
                        <gloss><q>to be proud</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>si-kad-uli</w>
                        <gloss><q>fame</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>pride</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>kad</w>
                        <gloss><q>prize</q></gloss></mentioned> is also thought of as close to
                    Ossetic (%bГ е н к о, ЗКВ V 722%b). — Other etymologies: %bШегрен%b (84) —
                    Arabic %iqadr%i ‘price’, ‘dignity’; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>(II 49)</biblScope></bibl>: „it
                    might be close to Avestian %ikāta-%i ‘favourite’, ‘loving’, a passive participle
                    from %ikā-%i ‘to wish’“. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kadæg"/>,<ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_koj"/>,<ref type="xr" target="#entry_kīnæ"/>,<ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_cyt"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævǵīd"
                    />.</etym>
            </entry>
        </body>
